The article discusses the progress made in the Major Economies Forum on Energy and Climate, with the release of ten new Technology Action Plans. President Obama launched this forum in 2009 to address climate change and promote clean energy. The Global Partnership, established during the summit in Italy, focuses on clean energy technologies. The Technology Action Plans outline government actions in areas such as advanced vehicles, bioenergy, and wind energy. Energy Secretary Steven Chu has been asked to enhance cooperation with other countries to implement these recommendations.